{"timestamp":"2026-03-05T11:17:58.828Z","hookEventName":"PreToolUse","sessionId":"83c0e933-a323-4d97-94fb-c0295499efd5","transcript_path":"/Users/alexl70/Library/Application Support/Code/User/workspaceStorage/b21d2b2c4133de2eb22354a8d6c6e00a/GitHub.copilot-chat/transcripts/83c0e933-a323-4d97-94fb-c0295499efd5.jsonl","tool_name":"multi_replace_string_in_file","tool_input":{"explanation":"Remove all auth-duplicating content from AGENTS.md: §5.4, the JWT localStorage bullet in §6.4, §6.5, and two auth bullets in §8. Renumber affected sections accordingly.","replacements":[{"filePath":"/Volumes/transcend/src/pet/linkshortener/AGENTS.md","oldString":"### 5.4 Authentication & JWT\n\n- JWT tokens are stateless. Do not store session state server-side beyond the transient OAuth state cookie.\n- JWT claims must include: `user_id`, `user_name`, `sub`, `iat`, `exp`.\n- All protected endpoints must be guarded by JWT middleware that validates the `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header.\n- `gorilla/sessions` store is used exclusively for the duration of the OAuth2 redirect/callback flow and must be cleared immediately after the callback completes. The `gorilla/sessions` store MUST NEVER BE USED OTHERWISE in the application.\n\n### 5.5 Logging","newString":"### 5.4 Logging"},{"filePath":"/Volumes/transcend/src/pet/linkshortener/AGENTS.md","oldString":"### 5.6 Performance","newString":"### 5.5 Performance"},{"filePath":"/Volumes/transcend/src/pet/linkshortener/AGENTS.md","oldString":"### 6.4 State Management\n\n- Global shared state (auth token, user info, URL list) lives in Pinia stores under `src/stores/`.\n- Do not use `localStorage` directly in components. Wrap all persistence in Pinia store actions.\n- JWT tokens may be stored in `localStorage` only through the auth store.","newString":"### 6.4 State Management\n\n- Global shared state (auth token, user info, URL list) lives in Pinia stores under `src/stores/`.\n- Do not use `localStorage` directly in components. Wrap all persistence in Pinia store actions."},{"filePath":"/Volumes/transcend/src/pet/linkshortener/AGENTS.md","oldString":"### 6.5 Routing & Guards\n\n- All routes that require authentication must have a `beforeEnter` guard (or a global `beforeEach` guard) that checks for a valid JWT via the auth store.\n- Unauthenticated users must be redirected to the home page.\n- After successful login, users must be redirected to the dashboard page.\n\n### 6.6 Styling","newString":"### 6.5 Styling"},{"filePath":"/Volumes/transcend/src/pet/linkshortener/AGENTS.md","oldString":"## 8. Security Rules (must be implemented before any public release)\n\n- **No passwords stored.** Authentication is exclusively through OAuth2/OIDC third-party providers.\n- **Input validation:**","newString":"## 8. Security Rules (must be implemented before any public release)\n\n- **Input validation:**"},{"filePath":"/Volumes/transcend/src/pet/linkshortener/AGENTS.md","oldString":"- **Monthly quotas:** Redirect processing enforces the monthly click quota per user before recording the click.\n- **HTTP-only, SameSite cookies** must be used for the OAuth state session.\n- Never expose stack traces","newString":"- **Monthly quotas:** Redirect processing enforces the monthly click quota per user before recording the click.\n- Never expose stack traces"}]},"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NBhHxSydA2kuF4W7ihwDab__vscode-1772706677409","cwd":"/Volumes/transcend/src/pet/linkshortener"}

