{"timestamp":"2026-03-05T13:39:19.884Z","hookEventName":"PreToolUse","sessionId":"08759084-6d18-42c0-b93b-0fd1a2c4a581","transcript_path":"/Users/alexl70/Library/Application Support/Code/User/workspaceStorage/b21d2b2c4133de2eb22354a8d6c6e00a/GitHub.copilot-chat/transcripts/08759084-6d18-42c0-b93b-0fd1a2c4a581.jsonl","tool_name":"multi_replace_string_in_file","tool_input":{"explanation":"Apply all changes to both files simultaneously: move unique frontend-component content into frontend-components.md (renumbering sections), and clean up AGENTS.md by removing duplicates, removing moved content, and renaming the section that loses its primary rule.","replacements":[{"filePath":"/Volumes/transcend/src/pet/linkshortener/ai-instructions/frontend-components.md","oldString":"---\n\n## 5. What Agents Must Not Do\n\n- Do not create any new file under `src/components/` manually; only the shadcn/vue CLI may place files there.\n- Do not build custom form inputs, buttons, modals, tables, tooltips, badges, or any other UI primitive from scratch when a shadcn/vue equivalent exists.\n- Do not introduce any additional UI component library (e.g., Vuetify, PrimeVue, Element Plus, Headless UI) — shadcn/vue and Tailwind CSS are the only permitted UI tools.\n- Do not use inline `style` attributes for static values; express all styling through Tailwind CSS utility classes.","newString":"---\n\n## 5. Component Authoring Standards\n\n- All Vue components (`src/views/` and `src/custom-components/`) must use `<script setup lang=\"ts\">`. The Options API is not permitted.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Styling\n\n- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes exclusively. Do not write custom CSS anywhere except `src/style.css` for global base styles.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Testing\n\n- shadcn/vue components installed into `src/components/` are excluded from test coverage requirements, as they are used as-is without customization. They may still be covered by tests when the consuming component's logic requires it (e.g., conditional rendering based on props). If you find any contradiction about it, report it immediately and start a discussion.\n\n---\n\n## 8. What Agents Must Not Do\n\n- Do not create any new file under `src/components/` manually; only the shadcn/vue CLI may place files there.\n- Do not build custom form inputs, buttons, modals, tables, tooltips, badges, or any other UI primitive from scratch when a shadcn/vue equivalent exists.\n- Do not introduce any additional UI component library (e.g., Vuetify, PrimeVue, Element Plus, Headless UI) — shadcn/vue and Tailwind CSS are the only permitted UI tools.\n- Do not use inline `style` attributes for static values; express all styling through Tailwind CSS utility classes."},{"filePath":"/Volumes/transcend/src/pet/linkshortener/AGENTS.md","oldString":"### 6.1 Composition API Only\n\n- All components use `<script setup lang=\"ts\">`. Options API is not permitted.\n- Reactive state lives in `ref` or `reactive`. Avoid direct mutation of Pinia state outside of store actions.","newString":"### 6.1 Reactive State\n\n- Reactive state lives in `ref` or `reactive`. Avoid direct mutation of Pinia state outside of store actions."},{"filePath":"/Volumes/transcend/src/pet/linkshortener/AGENTS.md","oldString":"### 6.3 Component Structure\n\n- shadcn/vue components belong in `src/components/`.\n- Page-level components (one per route) belong in `src/views/`.\n- shadcn/vue components are copied into the project and used \"as is\" without any customization. If you find the case where sticking to this rule leads to considerable code duplication or complexity, report it immediately and start the discussion about how to handle the situation.","newString":"### 6.3 Component Structure\n\n- shadcn/vue components belong in `src/components/`.\n- Page-level components (one per route) belong in `src/views/`."},{"filePath":"/Volumes/transcend/src/pet/linkshortener/AGENTS.md","oldString":"### 6.5 Styling\n\n- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes exclusively. Do not write custom CSS except in `src/style.css` for global base styles.\n- Do not use inline `style` attributes for anything other than truly dynamic values that cannot be expressed with Tailwind.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Testing Standards","newString":"---\n\n## 7. Testing Standards"},{"filePath":"/Volumes/transcend/src/pet/linkshortener/AGENTS.md","oldString":"- CSS, animations, and third-party SDK integrations are excluded from coverage requirements.\n- Imported shadcn/vue that are installed into `frontend/src/components/` are excluded from testing as they are used \"as is\" without any customization. Still they might be covered by tests if they are used in a way that requires some logic to be tested (e.g., conditional rendering based on props). If you find any contradiction about it, report it immediately and start a discussion about how to handle the situation.","newString":"- CSS, animations, and third-party SDK integrations are excluded from coverage requirements."},{"filePath":"/Volumes/transcend/src/pet/linkshortener/AGENTS.md","oldString":"- Do not bypass Huma registration for API endpoints.\n- Do not use the Options API in Vue components.\n- Do not alter existing database migrations; create new ones instead.","newString":"- Do not bypass Huma registration for API endpoints.\n- Do not alter existing database migrations; create new ones instead."}]},"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TbAHcHWBxdGL9nMsLLW8JY__vscode-1772706677419","cwd":"/Volumes/transcend/src/pet/linkshortener"}

